aces as identified in second language acquisition. The study will appeal to researchers interested in second and third language acquisition, bi- and multilingualism and crosslinguistic influence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aDiscourse analysisxSocial aspectszChina. 0aIntercultural communicationzChinazHong KongvCross-cultural studies. 0aLanguage acquisitionvCross-cultural studies. 0aLanguages in contactzChinazHong KongvCross-cultural studies. 0aMultilingualismzChinazHong KongvCross-cultural studies. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aBackward transfer.  aChinese learners of English and French.  aCrosslinguistic influence.  aFeature-reassembly Hypothesis.  aInterface Hypothesis.  aL3A.  aMultilingualism.  aPotential reverse transfer.  aReverse transfer.  aSLA.  aScalpel Model of Third Language Acquisition.  aSecond language acquisition.  aThird language acquisition.  aTransfer.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066311208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309689340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783096893423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783096893/original  a978-3-11-060670-6  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-064982-6  Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-066311-2  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  